==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek (phantasma), via Latin [[phantasma]] then Old French [[fantasme]].

===Noun===
'''phantom''' ([[phantoms]])

#Something [[apparently]] [[seen]], [[heard]], or [[sense]]d, but having no [[physical]] [[reality]]; a [[ghost]] or [[apparition]]; something [[elusive]] or [[delusive]]
#An [[image]] that appears only in the [[mind]]; an [[illusion]]

